@node "introduction" "Introduction"

 @{b}INTRODUCTION@{ub}

 This is a program to display system (computer) configuration.
 And it also contains a Bug Reporter, almost two programs in one =)

 I wanted a program to display my computer configuration in a very
 easy read way, and also be able to "dump" all info to an ASCII file.

@endnode

@node "installation" "Installation"

 @{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}

 Installer script is not available, but you don't need it either.

 But if someone want's to write it for me, please do so.

 Contact @{"Author",link "author"}

@endnode

@node "startingprogram" "Starting What-Config"

 @{b}STARTING PROGRAM@{ub}

 @{b}What-Config v1.3@{ub} can be started both from Workbench and Shell.

 Supported Tooltypes (WORKBENCH)

 Ę @{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub}

   Name of public screen to open the interface on.

 Ę @{b} CX_POPUP@{ub}

   Open or keep the user interface closed.

   CX_POPUP=TRUE or CX_POPUP=FALSE.

 Supported Arguments (SHELL)

 Ę @{b}PUBSCREEN@{ub}

   Name of public screen to open the interface on.

 Ę @{b} CX_POPUP@{ub}

   Open or keep the user interface closed.

   CX_POPUP=TRUE or CX_POPUP=FALSE.

@endnode
@node "usage" "Usage"

 @{b}USAGE@{ub}

  @{b}MAIN WINDOW (BUTTONS)@{ub}

  @{b}Ę Boards@{ub}

    Show expansion boards.

  @{b}Ę About@{ub}

    Information about the program.

  @{b}Ę Quit@{ub}

    Well.. you figure it out!

  @{b}MAIN WINDOW (MENUS)@{ub}

  @{b}Ę Hide@{ub}

    Close window, can be opened by selecting "What? Config v1.4" in Tools-Menu.

  @{b}Ę About@{ub}

    Information about the program.

  @{b}Ę Quit@{ub}

    Well.. you figure it out!

  @{b}Ę Create Bug Report@{ub}

    Open the Bug Report Editor.

  @{b}Ę Save List@{ub}

    @{b}Ę Short List@{ub}

      Save a SHORT list (the most important things).

    @{b}Ę Full List@{ub}

      Save a COMPLETE list of expansions that identify.library has to offer :-).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  @{b}BOARDS WINDOW@{ub}

  @{b}Ę Close@{ub}

    Hmmm, close the window perhaps?

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  @{b}Bug Report Window@{ub}

  @{b}Ę Program Name@{ub}

    The program name that contains the bug(s).

  @{b}Ę Version@{ub}

    Version of program.

  @{b}Ę Author@{ub}

    The Authors name (the person who wrote it).

Ā @{b}Ę Bug Priority@{ub}

    5 modes [Highest/High/Normal/Low/Lowest], You choose.

    If a program keeps crashing/causing gurus the priority should be set
    to "Highest".

  @{b}Ę Include Commodities List@{ub}

    Include a list of runnings Commodities in Bug Report output.

  @{b}Ę Include Full List@{ub}

    Save a Complete list of expansions that identify.library has to offer.

    @{b}Error Description@{ub}

    -> Textfield.gadget <-

    Yes, Error Description. describe what you were doing etc.

  @{b}Ę Save@{ub}

    Save Bug Report to ASCII file.

  @{b}Ę User Info@{ub}

    You should enter your name here, along with other important information, this
    part will also be included in the Bug Report output.

  @{b}Ę Cancel@{ub}

    Close the Bug Report window, and clear everything.

 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  @{b}USER INFO WINDOW@{ub}Ę

  @{b}Ę Name@{ub}

    Your name.

  @{b}Ę Street@{ub}

    Street adress.

  @{b}Ę Zip, City@{ub}

    Zip code, and city name.

  @{b}Ę Country@{ub}

    The country you live in.

  @{b}Ę Phone@{ub}

    Your phonenumber.

  @{b}Ę E-Mail@{ub}

    Your e-mail.

  @{b}Ę Misc@{ub}

    Comment or whatever you want.

  @{b}Ę Save@{ub}

    Save all info to a file ".WC_Configuration" which will be saved in PROGDIR:

  @{b}Ę Cancel@{ub}

    Close the User Info window.

 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  @{b}ABOUT WINDOW@{ub}

   @{b}Ę Close@{ub}

     When you're tired of watching my E-MAIL/ICQ addresses :-)

@endnode
@node "features" "Features"

 @{b}What-Config - FEATURES@{ub}

 Ę Program have a font-sensitive user interface.
 Ę Can be opened on any public Screen. (Tooltype/ReadArgs())
 Ę Has a Bug Report Editor built-in.
 Ę Attaches itself to Tools-Menu (AppMenuItem).
 Ę Program is now a Commodity.
 Ę Easy-to-Use

@endnode
@node "requirements" "Requirements"

 @{b}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

 This program needs atleast kickstart v2.04+

 @{b}Ę@{ub} gtlayout.library 40+     (INCLUDED)

 @{b}Ę@{ub} reqtools.library v38+

 @{b}Ę@{ub} @{"identify.library v9+" LINK identify}    (INCLUDED)

 @{b}Ę@{ub} textfield.gadget v0+

 To keep the archive size down I've decided not to include all of the libraries.
 But you can find all of them on Aminet.

 Or you can E-Mail me and I'll send them to you.

@endnode
@node "history" "History"

 @{b}HISTORY@{ub}

 @{b}v1.0 -> v1.1@{ub}

 Internal versions.

 @{b}v1.2@{ub}

 First Aminet release.

 @{b}v1.3@{ub}

 BUGFIX: If the @{b}User Info@{ub} fields was empty and trying to create a bug report
         enforcer hits would appear. This is hopefully fixed. reported by Tony  Preston.

 BUGFIX: GTST_MaxChars was not added to all "StringGadgets" (Shame on me).
         But now they are =)

 UPDATE: The document guide has gone trough some cosmetic changes.

 @{b}v1.4@{ub}


  ADDED: `support' for PPC. So if you have PPC your window will get some more info.

  ADDED: `CPU clock' / `FPU clock' to Main Window. (Mhz).

  ADDED: Possibility to include the FULL Expansion list to Bug Report.

  ADDED: Program can be exited by pressing CTRL+C.

  ADDED: Added Commodity/AppMenu Support.
   NOTE: Default is CX_POPUP=TRUE

 UPDATE: Rewrote about 50% of the code.

@endnode
